{{More citations needed|article|date=February 2008}} {{Infobox person | name = Abraham Abell | image = | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth date|1789|04|11}} | birth_place = {{flag|Ireland}} [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[Ireland]] | death_date = 1851 | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = {{flag|Ireland}} | other_names = | known_for = | education = | employer = | occupation = [[Antiquarian]] | title = | salary = | networth = | height = | weight = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | signature = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Abraham Abell''' (April 11, 1789 &ndash; 1851) was an [[Irish people|Irish]] [[antiquarian]].
==Early career== Abell was born in [[Cork (city)|Cork]], [[Ireland]], into a [[Quaker]] family of eleven children. His family had long standing in business. He also was successful in business and noted for his charity. He served as treasurer of the Cork Dispensary and Humane Society.<ref name=monthly>[https://books.google.com/books?id=P2g3AAAAMAAJ&pg=PA319&lpg=PA319&dq=abraham+abell+cork&source=bl&ots=8qbaXFAyEM&sig=VSxoXbTzfZ7ee_Pz77yAOXSAy5c&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCgQ6AEwAmoVChMIxZuppNfBxwIVw3o-Ch3rgAA6#v=onepage&q=abraham%20abell%20cork&f=false Coleman, James. "Abraham Abbal", ''The Irish Monthly'', Vol. 26, 1898]</ref>
==Cultural interests== He had a great interest in [[archaeology]] and did a study of the [[Irish Round Tower]]. He was responsible for the first collection of [[Ogham]] stone inscriptions and his collection is now on public display at [[University College Cork]]. He had a major collection of books. He was a member of the [[Royal Cork Institution]] and one of the founders in 1835 of the [[Cuvierian Society]].<ref name=monthly/> This was the forerunner of the Cork Historical and Archaeological Society.
At the time of his death, Abell's personal library contained about 4,500 volumes, including books written in [[Italian language|Italian]], [[French language|French]], [[Latin language|Latin]], [[German language|German]], [[Spanish language|Spanish]], [[Greek language|Greek]], [[Hebrew]], and [[Irish language|Irish]].
